    ('PHIL-P 106', 'INTRODUCTION TO PROBLEMS OF PHILOSOPHY', '9623', 'Class Status', 'MW Monday, Wednesday 12:45 PM–1:35 PM', 'LH 102', 'Timothy O''Connor', 2, 'Lecture', 'Lecture', '3', 'LINDLEY HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Covers perennial problems of philosophy, particularly in ethics, metaphysics, and epistemology (e.g., the self, personal identity, knowledge, existence, reality, God, and the good life). Engages historical and contemporary primary resources. Concentrates on reading and interpretation of original philosophical texts, the evaluation of philosophical argumentation, and the development of philosophical skills.', ARRAY['IUB GenEd A&H credit
COLL (CASE) A&H Breadth of Inquiry credit'], NULL),
