COLL INTENSIVE WRITING SECTIONS'], NULL),
    ('PHIL-P 301', 'MEDIEVAL PHILOSOPHY', '13247', 'Class Status', 'MW Monday, Wednesday 2:20 PM–3:35 PM', 'BH 242', 'Rega Wood', 1, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'BALLANTINE HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'A selective survey of Western philosophy from the turn of the Christian era to the end of the Middle Ages. Readings from some or all of: Augustine, Boethius, Anselm, Abelard, Bonaventure, Aquinas, Duns Scotus, and Ockham.', ARRAY['COLL (CASE) A&H Breadth of Inquiry credit
COLL (CASE) Culture Studies: Global Civ & Culture'], NULL),
    ('PHIL-P 312', 'TOPICS IN THEORY OF KNOWLEDGE', '11090', 'Closed', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 2:20 PM–3:35 PM', 'WH 008', 'Gary Ebbs', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'WOODBURN HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Topics such as various theories of perceptual realism, sense-datum theories, theories of appearing, phenomenalism, the nature of knowledge, the relation between knowledge and belief, of knowledge and evidence, and the problem of skepticism.', ARRAY['COLL (CASE) A&H Breadth of Inquiry credit'], NULL),
    ('PHIL-P 340', 'CLASSICS IN ETHICS', '13248', 'Closed', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 12:45 PM–2:00 PM', 'SY 001', 'Katy Abramson', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'SYCAMORE HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Readings from Plato and Aristotle to Kant, Mill, and Nietzsche. Topics include virtue and human nature, pleasure and the good, the role of reason in ethics, the objectivity of moral principles, and the relation of religion to ethics.', ARRAY['COLL (CASE) A&H Breadth of Inquiry credit
COLL INTENSIVE WRITING SECTIONS'], NULL),
    ('PHIL-P 345', 'PROBLEMS IN SOCIAL AND POLITICAL PHILOSOPHY', '13250', 'Class Status', 'MW Monday, Wednesday 12:45 PM–2:00 PM', 'BH 144', 'Matthew Adams', 2, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'BALLANTINE HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL, ARRAY['COLL (CASE) A&H Breadth of Inquiry credit'], NULL),
    ('PHIL-P 352', 'LOGIC AND PHILOSOPHY', '29441', 'Class Status', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 11:10 AM–12:25 PM', 'WH 005', 'Calum McNamara', 26, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'WOODBURN HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Relation of logic to other areas of philosophy. Selected topics from among the following: logic and ontology; logic and language; logic, reasoning, and belief; intentionality and intentional logic; tense and modal logic; individuation, reference, identity.', ARRAY['COLL (CASE) A&H Breadth of Inquiry credit'], NULL),
    ('PHIL-P 366', 'PHILOSOPHY OF ACTION', '29442', 'Class Status', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 3:55 PM–5:10 PM', 'BH 343', 'Kirk Ludwig', 9, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'BALLANTINE HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'The nature of human and rational action; the structure of intentions and practical consciousness; the role of the self in action; volitions; the connections of desires, needs, and purposes to intentions and doings; causation and motivation; freedom; the structure of deliberation; rational actions and duties, whether moral or institutional.', ARRAY['COLL (CASE) A&H Breadth of Inquiry credit'], NULL),
    ('PHIL-P 370', 'TOPICS IN PHILOSOPHY', '29453', 'Class Status', 'MW Monday, Wednesday 3:55 PM–5:10 PM', 'I 107', 'Katy Meadows', 14, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'MYLES BRAND HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'A survey of selected topics or figures in an area of philosophy (area will vary).', ARRAY['COLL (CASE) A&H Breadth of Inquiry credit'], NULL),
    ('PHIL-P 401', 'HISTORY OF PHILOSOPHY: SPECIAL TOPICS', '13252', 'Class Status', 'MW Monday, Wednesday 2:20 PM–3:35 PM', 'SY 003', 'Allen Wood', 2, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'SYCAMORE HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'A focused look at a particular thinker, movement, period, or set of ideas in the history of philosophy.', ARRAY['COLL (CASE) A&H Breadth of Inquiry credit'], NULL),
    ('PHIL-P 498', 'HONORS THESIS DIRECTED RESEARCH', '2806', 'Class Status', NULL, NULL, 'Adam Leite', 8, NULL, 'Readings', '4', NULL, ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Directed research course preparatory to writing the senior honors thesis. Training in skills necessary for original philosophical research. Goals are to achieve appropriate mastery over a body of philosophical material relevant to the honors thesis project, and to develop core ideas for a successful honors thesis.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('PHIL-P 499', 'HONORS THESIS', '2807', 'Class Status', NULL, NULL, 'Adam Leite', 9, NULL, 'Readings', '3–6', NULL, ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL, ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('PHIL-P 500', 'PROSEMINAR', '6672', 'Class Status', 'Tu Tuesday 4:45 PM–7:15 PM', 'SY 022', 'David Sussman', 6, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'SYCAMORE HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Professional seminar for entering graduate students that concentrates on philosophical writing and seminar participation.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('PHIL-P 505', 'LOGICAL THEORY I', '2808', 'Class Status', 'W Wednesday 4:45 PM–7:15 PM', 'SY 022', 'Sharon Berry', 12, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'SYCAMORE HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'A survey of modern logic consisting of syntactic and semantic (proof-theoretic and model-theoretic) treatments of the propositional and predicate calculi.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
